  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key aspects include:\n\n1. Reporting requirements for financial institutions\n2. Customer due diligence procedures\n3. Suspicious transaction monitoring\n4. Financial record keeping\n5. Know Your Customer (KYC) guidelines\n\nMajor examples include:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) in the United States\n- EU Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) international standards\n\nFinancial institutions must comply with these regulations to help prevent financial crimes.",
